§ Definition ⦉
¶ ⦊
  ‖ A polynomial is ❬symmetric❭ if its value is unchanged under
    all permutations of its arguments. ⦉

  ‖ I.e., a polynomial $f: 𝗥^n → 𝗥$ is symmetric if
    ◇ ⦊
      ‖ f(x) = f(x ∘ g) \quad \text{for all permutations } g
        \text{ of } \set{1, …, n} ⦉
    ⦉⦉
⦉

§§ Example ⦉
¶ ⦊
  ‖ The polynomial $f: 𝗥^n → 𝗥$ defined by
    ◇ ⦊
      ‖ f(x_1, …, x_n) = x_1 + x_2 + ⋯ + x_n \quad \text{for
        all } x_1, …, x_n ∈ 𝗥 ⦉
    ⦉
    is symmetric. ⦉
